resource.name: Operating Budget Revenue Data
resource.description:
The county’s estimated revenue sources for the current budget, including property tax levy, intergovernmental revenue, charges for services and other sources. 

Ramsey County uses a two-year (biennial) operating budget. An operating budget is created for the first year of the budget cycle and is monitored to continually improve the county’s financial management and strategic planning efforts. Additional resolutions and amendments may increase or decrease certain funding sources, so a supplemental budget for the second year is submitted to the Ramsey County Board of Commissioners for approval.

You can view the county’s financial reports and additional resources at ramseycounty.us/budget.
columns_description: Dollars initially allocated in budget approved by County Board
Dollars currently allocated to this item

domain_metadata.value: Property tax levy and fund balance are managed in Finance spreadsheets.  Other revenue sources are managed in Aspen and loaded into Hyperion.  This dataset is created from extracts from Aspen appended to data from the Levy/Fund Balance spreadsheets.
